			<common:generalComment xml:lang="en">Rubber powder is used in various industries due to its physical and chemical properties. It is particularly utilized in construction for adhesives, sealants, and coatings, and in the automotive sector for parts that require resistance to vibration, weather, heat, oil, and fuel. The addition of rubber powder to clay mixtures affects the compression ratio (Cr), with higher percentages of rubber powder increasing the Cr value. This indicates its impact on the material's elasticity and compressibility. Studies on rubber powder focus on its physicochemical characterization and thermal analysis, which are essential for developing processing methods, designing products, and predicting performance. The use of recycled rubber powder (RRP) is growing in the rubber industry to enhance sustainability.</common:generalComment>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="zh">橡胶粉由于其物理和化学性质而被应用于各种行业。它特别用于粘合剂、密封剂和涂料的建筑，以及汽车行业中需要耐振动、耐候、耐热、耐油和耐燃料的零件。向粘土混合物中添加橡胶粉会影响压缩比（Cr），橡胶粉的百分比越高，Cr值越高。这表明其对材料弹性和压缩性的影响。胶粉的研究重点是其物理化学特性和热分析，这对开发加工方法、设计产品和预测性能至关重要。再生胶粉（RRP）在橡胶行业的使用越来越多，以提高可持续性。</common:generalComment>
